<span id="freeTextContainer18308116543442772698">Iconoclastic &amp; surreal &amp; immediate, this meditation, this fantasia on national themes, probably gets better with age. As the tragedy of HIV/AIDS at its inception in the middle of the Western world becomes more pronounced, even more beautifully terrifying--a seed that will germinate (MUST!) in all members and future members of the LGBtQIA+ community. As Part One ends in a fascinating hyperbolic HALELLUJAH! I cannot even fathom a better link to, a more fanatical search for and more angsty wait for</span>
  <span id="freeText18308116543442772698" style="display:none">Iconoclastic &amp; surreal &amp; immediate, this meditation, this fantasia on national themes, probably gets better with age. As the tragedy of HIV/AIDS at its inception in the middle of the Western world becomes more pronounced, even more beautifully terrifying--a seed that will germinate (MUST!) in all members and future members of the LGBtQIA+ community. As Part One ends in a fascinating hyperbolic HALELLUJAH! I cannot even fathom a better link to, a more fanatical search for and more angsty wait for, Part Two of the meteoric American theater God.</span>
