<div id="review_3489030149" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3489030149" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/628167-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1475189725p2/628167.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3489030149?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/628167-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3489030149" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17659446418753375050">I listened to the National Theatre cast audiobook and it was so impressive. It addresses a lot of really important social and political issues as well as some close to home cultural heartaches. The content is pretty harsh with certain characters who love the f-bomb and a sex scene. I personally tried to avoid those where I could. But I understand the importance of this work even if I’m not sure I can finish part 2. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


